snippet.textDisplay:
I have asked my insurance company and they said they do not care where the car is registered, only where it is garaged. If you live in CA but register in MT and insure it for MT you can get into trouble and get your claim denied. On the flip side if you register it in MT and insure it for CA there’s less likelihood they will deny claims. Have you ever noticed that insurance never asks for your license plate or where it’s registered? They only care where it will be operated and stored.

Also, South Dakota will register your car as an individual, without setting up a shell company. They also do street legal titles for dirt bikes 👀.

If you live in CA, and purchase a Skyline, for example, it will not pass emissions testing. There is only ONE location that is authorized to do the conversions, and someone in this video is affiliated with that location. That cost: $10,000.

By creating public awareness, those affiliated with making laws can legislate and attempt to close this legal loophole.

When it does, where can you get your R32 GTR California compliant? Well, at the one and only place that is authorized in California to do the conversion. At a cost of $10,000 of course.
